io.github.hhromic.uimr.as

Class ASObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.hhromic.uimr.as.ASObject
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Activity

    public class ASObject
extends Object

    This class represents an Activity Streams Object.

    This class is a direct representation of the JSON Serialization provided from the Activity Streams website in http://activitystrea.ms/specs/json/1.0/#object.

    Since:
    4.0
    Author:
    Hugo Hromic

    • Field Detail

      • attachments

        protected ASObject[] attachments

        A collection of one or more additional, associated objects, similar to the concept of attached files in an email message. An ASObject MAY have an attachments property whose value is an Array of ASObjects.

      • author

        protected ASObject author

        Describes the entity that created or authored the ASObject. An ASObject MAY contain a single author property whose value is an ASObject of any type. Note that the author field identifies the entity that created the ASObject and does not necessarily identify the entity that published the ASObject. For instance, it may be the case that an object created by one person is posted and published to a system by an entirely different entity.

      • content

        protected String content

        Natural-language description of the ASObject encoded as a single String containing HTML markup. Visual elements such as thumbnail images MAY be included. An ASObject MAY contain a content property.

      • displayName

        protected String displayName

        A natural-language, human-readable and plain-text name for the ASObject. HTML markup MUST NOT be included. An ASObject MAY contain a displayName property. If the ASObject does not specify an objectType property, the ASObject SHOULD specify a displayName.

      • downstreamDuplicates

        protected String[] downstreamDuplicates

        An Array of one or more absolute IRI's [RFC3987] identifying ASObjects that duplicate this ASObject's content. An ASObject SHOULD contain a downstreamDuplicates property when there are known ASObjects, possibly in a different system, that duplicate the content in this ASObject. This MAY be used as a hint for consumers to use when resolving duplicates between ASObjects received from different sources.

      • id

        protected String id

        Provides a permanent, universally unique identifier for the ASObject in the form of an absolute IRI [RFC3987]. An ASObject SHOULD contain a single id property. If an ASObject does not contain an id property, consumers MAY use the value of the url property as a less-reliable, non-unique identifier.

      • image

        protected MediaLink image

        Description of a resource providing a visual representation of the ASObject, intended for human consumption. An ASObject MAY contain an image property whose value is a MediaLink.

      • objectType

        protected String objectType

        Identifies the type of ASObject. An ASObject MAY contain an objectType property whose value is a String that is non-empty and matches either the "isegment-nz-nc" or the "IRI" production in [RFC3987]. Note that the use of a relative reference other than a simple name is not allowed. If no objectType property is contained, the ASObject has no specific type.

      • published

        protected Date published

        The date and time at which the ASObject was published. An ASObject MAY contain a published property.

      • summary

        protected String summary

        Natural-language summarization of the ASObject encoded as a single String containing HTML markup. Visual elements such as thumbnail images MAY be included. An Activity MAY contain a summary property.

      • updated

        protected Date updated

        The date and time at which a previously published ASOject has been modified. An ASObject MAY contain an updated property.

      • upstreamDuplicates

        protected String[] upstreamDuplicates

        An Array of one or more absolute IRI's [RFC3987] identifying ASObjects that duplicate this ASObject's content. An ASObject SHOULD contain an upstreamDuplicates property when a publisher is knowingly duplicating with a new ID the content from another ASObject. This MAY be used as a hint for consumers to use when resolving duplicates between ASObjects received from different sources.

      • url

        protected String url

        An IRI [RFC3987] identifying a resource providing an HTML representation of the ASObject. An ASObject MAY contain a url property.
